The paper deals with the analysis of large-scale network data using relational event models, which are commonly used in social network analysis and related fields. The paper discusses the reliability of parameter estimates under different sampling schemes and provides experimental results using data from the Wikipedia editing network. The paper is likely to be relevant to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity).
